This paper is about model-based reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper proposes a novel search-control strategy for the Dyna architecture, which is a model-based approach to reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the theoretical justification for the proposed approach, which suggests that it may be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
